      "writtenOn": "2018-01-08T19:28:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If both physics_load and physics_save are specified, the physics_load is silently discarded.  Maybe log a warning, or better yet error out if both options are specified?\n\nAdditionally, I think this it would be more readable if this was split out into if statements, such as:\n\nif (android_cmdLineOptions-\u003ephysics_save) {\n    // TODO: Check for physics_load and error out here, or error out earlier if both options are specified.\n    h-\u003ephysical_model \u003d physicalModel_new(true, android_cmdLineOptions-\u003ephysics_save, true);\n} else if (android_cmdLineOptions-\u003ephysics_load) {\n    h-\u003ephysical_model \u003d physicalModel_new(true, android_cmdLineOptions-\u003ephysics_load, false);\n} else {\n    h-\u003ephysical_model \u003d physicalModel_new(true, NULL, false);\n}",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 845,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 848,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "86bd99c5b796ff5f359438926476387089d49d37",
